FRONTLINE ROADS v0.30.0 SYSTEM INTEGRITY AUDIT

Release: 0.30.0-system-integrity
Baseline: 0.29.1-display-recovery

PHASE 1 — OBSOLETE OUTPOST REMOVAL
- Resource-outpost implementation module removed.
- Canonical state, renderer, UI, production and Service Worker references removed.
- Two compatibility-only field-discard operations remain for old saves.

PHASE 2 — PROGRESSION
- Simple-base location freshness: 5 minutes.
- Simple-base road placement tolerance: 100 m.
- Simple-base construction anchor after establishment: 50 m.
- Hostile-base declared rewards are secured in one recoverable field cache.
- Resource-base replacement: 45–75 minutes.
- Copper / tin / iron rewards support mandatory Lv.3 and Lv.4 production chains.
- Attack-only opening regression remains constrained because destruction alone does not grant cargo.

PHASE 3 — COMBAT CONSISTENCY
- Doctrine affects route and target selection.
- Congestion-aware evasion enabled.
- Live defense ranges used for tower avoidance.
- Declared 30% / 35% / 42% shield auras applied.
- New enemy classifications connected to friendly matchup calculations.
- Enemy visual radii restored.

PHASE 4 — BASE AND PRODUCTION CONSISTENCY
- Secondary major bases can be targeted, damaged, destroyed and rebuilt onsite.
- Major-base ruins occupy slots and block overlapping replacement construction.
- Specialist pursuit is range-bounded.
- Trial bronze is project-only and contribution-capped.

